by the discipline problem while they are planning the next phase of a raid.  Just my 2cp<br>
<br>
I believe that it would help with the discipline of everyone involved if there were someone to draw a line in the dirt and say this is how it is.  IE, with the flag and people crossing...having someone say from the get go &quot;This is the fighting boundry, let the pulls come to where I stand, anyone crossing this line will get a warning...3 warnings and we'll see you next raid&quot; or to that effect.  Gets the point across, but isn't too commanding about it.  <br>
<br>
As far as order goes, that person could get down right mean if they had to, but only if they had to.  I have a few ideas/suggestions should this idea go through, and I'd apply for the part, should it be created officially. <p>Good Journies,<BR>
Stonescale Thulefist<BR>
