Karana chapter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufayen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fayen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/26/01 1:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=120.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Enforcer</span><hr size=1> That doesn't sound like a really bad idea.  I am level 43 still (Soon to be 44!!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) and I can't go on the raids yet.  Anyway, correct me if I am wrong, but aren't the raids supposed to also be fun?  If you have some jerk there yelling at every little thing that goes wrong, that would not be much fun and I think some people might not even want to attend the raids anymore.  I am not sure how bad they can get with people listening, following directions, etc, but I just think you need to keep in mind, its just a game and its supposed to be fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Founder</span><br>  Posts: 536<br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/26/01 2:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=120.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Enforcer</span><hr size=1> It's not fun when some moron is auctioning all night to the same people, spamming up your screen while you are trying to read the raid leader's directions. It's not fun when the raid commander says 3 times to NOT go sit on the throne, and as soon as the room is entered, 5 people go sit on the throne. The reason these things are so bad on raids like this is the immense amount of death that can result from someone zigging when they should have zagged. Nothing like a 4 hour corpse recovery, with 50 bodies layed out because you a few on the raid weren't listening to the raid commander. <br>
<br>
And speaking as a raid commander, it's a lot less fun running a raid when you have to repeat yourself 4 times to keep people from doing something that could get everyone killed. <br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukanebic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kanebic</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/29/01 9:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=120.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Enforcer</span><hr size=1>      I agree wholeheartedly with you! There has to be an action of last resort to remove disruptive players that refuse to listen to the Raid Leader. <br>
     I was on the last Naggy raid and was appalled at the lack of discipline of some players. These players need to know that for the good of the rest of those on the raid that there will be consequences for disobeying the Raid Leaders instructions.<br>
      People should know by now that these rules are not only for the safety of all involved but also to ensure a successful raid. enough said? <br>
     I think we should tryout a Raid Enforcer if for no other reason than to free up the Raid Leader to plan the raid and not have to worry about enforcing raid guidelines and strategies.<br>
<br>
Kanebic Blacknight<br>
44th Paladin of Tunare<br>
