The group leaders should carry more responsibility with the raiding, I agree.  Downside is it's hard to take 50 people from all walks of life in various guilds and pick the leaders out of that group.  I can't recall who was picked at Vox for group leaders...i'm guessing FoF members, but I was only in 1 group out of the 10 there.  Anyway, to successfully pull of having disciplined raid leaders, they would have to be screened and/or chosen before hand.  That way the raid leaders would know that those people are reliable and wouldn't have to worry about keeping an eye on someone they just picked out of those that show up.  <br>
