<br>
Anyway, while in general I do agree with you and your ideas Haemish, I feel I need to disagree with your belief that Plane and Dragon raids are all the raids CoG should do.  As I understand it, one of the major concerns people were having was that their higher level people were jumping guilds to larger uber guilds and so they werent growing very much.  This problem will remain as long as we are limited to the lower end raids.  And make no mistake Planar raiding is the easiest of the types of raids out there.  Plane and Dragon raids are no longer the end game, now the end game is all about raids, but raids on the Dragon Necropolis, Kael Arena, ThurgB, Howling Stones, Chardok, Velk's Lab, Temple of Veeshan, Sirrens Grotto, you get the idea.  These raids are all generally more complex than Planar raids since many require you to dungeon crawl.  If you want to take on the rat city in DN for example you do not stop moving.<br>
