<br>
To do this or even go about doing this, we'd need people to run stuff.  Right now we're pretty short on volenteers, though I'm sure there are people out there that would love to attend a raid.  I know Lag and Flarren are probably stretched pretty tight with times running both dragon and planular raids.  They'd probably do a great job elsewhere, but I know from experience that running raids can and usually is very draining.  <br>
<br>
If we could train and teach people how to run raids, then we could do things like DN without spreading our resources too thin.  I know I've been slacking a bit in the Mixer event area, not that it's required, but being a guild leader is a big job in itself, let alone stacking events on top of all of that.  I'd love to run some more events...and once I get moved and settled I'll continue to at least try to hold them.  Only way to get good is through practice, and practice I will <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  <br>
