<br>
One thing tho is that you do not need to be 55+ for most of these little adventures.  DN can be done with just 2 groups.  No, you wont take out zlandicar, but you can do the tunnel and walk aways with both a nice look at the zone as well as some very fun fights and if you're lucky some nice loot.  As for levels, 50-55 works fine in here, and even sub 50.  I first went there with zellex at 49.  I'm sure if you dont mind potentially dying once or twice and have some courage even lower is possible.  If I had the chance I would certainly have gone in at a lower level as well.<br>
<br>
The thing to remember is that if you are willing to die some with or without rez, then no where is closed to you.  I made 50 3 months ago, and am now just 1 yellow into 52.  And thats with almost constant playing and raiding (I did take 1 weekend off for a anime convention in seattle <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  I may not have leveled much, but I can tell you I had a hell of a good time.  Yeah, my equipment makes most level 40's laugh, and many of my friends are now between 3 and 5 levels higher, but I have been and done things most people would say are impossible at my level.  I've run through Hate naked, as well as Sirens Grotto (Thanks to zellex showing my the way), I've explored ToV recently and been to most of the zones in the game (I will get the VP key one day!).  None of this is meant as bragging.  These are all pure statements of what can be done at any level if you are willing to take some risks.  If you are then the high level game is open to you at almost any level if you know what you're doing.  If you are not willing to risk, then much of the game is closed to you.  So perhaps our problem isnt so much making more raids and showing people how to do it, so much as changing attitudes?<br>
<br>
Now theres a thought to mull over.   How many risks are you willing to run to have fun?  And just what is your definition of fun?  Is spending 6 hours and 2 deaths to see a new zone fun?  Hmmm.  Now that might be interesting to find out.  Heh, I see a new thread coming up. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
